column5: Anyone been to these two places lately?  I know by October you can walk across their backs in the Etobicoke but anyone manage to get out there in the past few days?
They are in there thick buddy.....  so many I couldn't believe it, had them all to myself today as well.  Had to pick me up some RubA535 to get the pain down in my arms.....  Burt
I heard E-creek was so hot right now guys are leaving their hooks and line on shore; the salmon come by, tie the knot and set the hook themselves.
brought my AK47 down there yesturday to slay them all... its hot!
all talk but no salmon........Dynamite should do...  Check out www.Spoonpullers.com ...The Trollers Website - Home  It`s just lake Ontario reports though
i went to the Credit today and there were nothing but  i heard ppl catching them at lakeshore tho
Was a marshmellow treat left behind for their efforts? And no fin fights in the mean time

My experience,hwy 5 closes mid august! Why? the biggest rainshower around that date should be your best option to check it out!above #5 not below!!!!!! BTW,Did anyone get awiff of the air today? ITS TIME!!!!!!
none, I took a pic in "the area" today and all I could see was these fish sunning at the surface (so they are sunfish, right?)
this was monday off cornation 75 feet 35 down it was darker and starting to hook most of the others were the same except for 2 and the rainbows were very pink oh yeah on a red devil
